FIX 1: DISTINGUISHING C_p FROM delta_p
------------------------------------------------------------
  BC contribution term: C_p = log(p)*p/(p-1)
  Irrationality term:   delta_p = -log(||p*pi/10||) - log(p)
  These are DIFFERENT. C_p is used for the BC lower bound.
  delta_p is used for the finiteness/irrationality measure proof.
  The paper conflated them (source of error E2/E3 in M15).

  p    | C_p = log(p)*p/(p-1)      | delta_p = -log(||.||)-log(p) | C_p == delta_p?
  -----|---------------------------|------------------------------|----------------
     2 | 1.38629436111989062         | 0.296570876324497427          | NO (different)
     3 | 1.64791843300216454         | 1.7569719618657597            | NO (different)
    19 | 3.10801892245346493         | 0.530169507106881683          | NO (different)
   191 | 5.27991697240477003         | 0.169413749026156286          | NO (different)

  CONFIRMED: C_p != delta_p for all p in S_4

CERTIFIED C(S_4) = sum C_p (BC formula):
  C_   2 = 1.386294361119890618834464
  C_   3 = 1.647918433002164537092868
  C_  19 = 3.108018922453464930009529
