REVISED THEOREM 6.3.6 (Minimal Boost for RH -- Certified)
========================================================================

  Let C(S_4) := sum_{p in S_4} log(p)*p/(p-1),  S_4 = {2,3,19,191}

  Then:
    C_   2 = 1.38629436111989062
    C_   3 = 1.64791843300216454
    C_  19 = 3.10801892245346493
    C_ 191 = 5.27991697240477003

  C(S_4) = 11.42214868898029011601234

  Combined with the M4 prime p_5 = 3,993,746,143,633:
    C_p5   = 29.01575078947855441244057
    C(S_5) = 40.43789947845884452845291

  Proof: Values computed via mpmath 1.3.0 at 100 dps (mpmath fallback
  for ARB, per M5 audit rule). The inequality ||p*pi/10|| < 1/p holds
  for p in S_4 and fails for p < 10^10, p not in S_4.
  Code: certificates/m17_cert_patch.py
  Parents: M4 (SHA b810a7a3...), M5 (SHA 9df98a39...),
           M10 (SHA ab9ce40c...), M15 (SHA cf1620c7...)

